  "prompt": "How and how much is announcer Bruce Buffer of MMA Octagon paid?",
  "response": "Bruce Buffer, the iconic announcer for the UFC (Ultimate Fighting Championship), is well-known for his energetic and distinctive style of announcing fighters. His earnings can vary based on the event and his role, but generally, Bruce Buffer is paid quite well for his services.\n\nAlthough exact figures can fluctuate, Bruce Buffer reportedly earns around $50,000 per UFC event. For major pay-per-view events, his salary can be significantly higher, sometimes reaching up to $100,000. In addition to his per-event earnings, Buffer is involved in other business ventures and endorsements, which also contribute to his overall income.\n\nIt's important to note that these figures are estimates and can vary. Bruce Buffer's established reputation and long-standing affiliation with the UFC make him one of the most recognizable and well-compensated announcers in the world of mixed martial arts.",
